Two KCSE candidates from Kauma secondary in Kitui will sit their exams while in police custody for malicious damage of property. Peter Kyalo and David Musangi reportedly broke into a girls’ dormitory at Kyaani girls secondary and destroyed school fence and items in the dormitory worth Sh50,000. The two pleaded guilty before Kitui resident magistrate Johnstone Munguti. The case will be mentioned on November 15, 2018. KCSE will run from November 5 to November 30. Read: No phones, school visits during KCSE and KCPE, teachers warned Also read: KCSE exam begins with language practicals ahead of theory papers Click here for the latest political news 